# CREATE NUXT APP
npx create-nuxt-app <name>

Choose the package manager: Npm (feel free to go with yarn)
Choose UI framework: Vootstrap Vue
Choose custom server framework: Express
Choose nuxt.js modules: Axios + Progressive Web App (PWA) Support
Choose linting tools: ESLint + Prettier + Lint staged files
Choose test framework: Jest
Choose rendering mode: Universal (SSR)
Choose development tools: None (because I don't use VSCode)

Now we add custom scripts for the linter:
>     "lint-disable": "sed -i \"s/^[ \\t]*'@nuxtjs\\/eslint-module'/    \\/\\/ '@nuxtjs\\/eslint-module'/\" nuxt.config.js",
>     "lint-enable": "sed -i \"s/^[ \\t]*\\/\\/ '@nuxtjs\\/eslint-module'/    '@nuxtjs\\/eslint-module'/\" nuxt.config.js",
>     "lint-fix": "eslint --fix --ext .js,.vue --ignore-path .gitignore .",

We can start the app with `npm run dev` and access it at localhost:3000

# EXPRESS
Now let's implement the express server
We change /server/index.js

Install the dependencies with:
`npm i -S @nuxtjs/dotenv`
Modify nuxt.config.js with
`require('dotenv').config()` before module.export
and `@nuxtjs/dotenv` in the modules array

We then add a .env configuration file to store some values:
```
NUXT_HOST=127.0.0.1
NUXT_HTTP_PORT=3000
NUXT_HTTPS_PORT=3001
```

Deployed okay on localhost

# FETCH SOME COMMENTS
Create a folder reviews in pages, and index.vue in that folder.
=> Show index.vue
Create components Reviews and ReviewsItem
=> Show both
Create a folder routes in server, and a file reviews.js in that folder.
=> Show reviews.js (route)
Create a reviews.js in store
=> Show reviews.js (store)
Finally, allow CORS in nuxt.config.js by adding:
` proxy: true`
and
`proxy: {
    '/api': `${isProd ? `https://${process.env.NUXT_HOST}` : `http://${process.env.NUXT_HOST}`}:${isProd ? process.env.NUXT_HTTPS_PORT : process.env.NUXT_HTTP_PORT }`
  },
